The Masonic Temple is a historic Masonic temple located at Warrensburg, Johnson County, Missouri. It was built in 1893â€“1894, and is a rectangular three-story, Italianate style red brick building with extensive sandstone trim.  The building measures approximately 48 feet by 92 feet.
It was for many years the meeting hall of Corinthian Lodge # 265 (a local Masonic Lodge), but the lodge has subsequently moved to other premises.
It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1998.
